title.72: Star Wars: Jabba the Hutt - The Hunger of Princess Nampi (1995) #1

description.0: An extradimensional adventure! In the medieval land of Geshem, Wolverine is approached by Shaman (Professor X), to stop the homicidal rampage of a man known only as Beast. Wolverine must fight for the honor of Queen Rain…and for the safety of Geshem’s citizens!
description.1: Scarlet Spider becomes a New Warrior! And the timing couldn't be better- the terroristic Undertow attacks the team!
description.4: The payback for Wonder Man comes down to this! The combined strength of Force Works and the Avengers against the alien might of the Kree enforcers known as Starstealth! Who will come out on top?
description.6: Pete Wisdom takes Kitty Pryde along with him to London to investigate a message he received from an old friend...only to find the author dead!
description.7: A classic rivalry with an urban twist! The fight between Hulk and Abomination tears through the streets of New York, with no end in sight! Can the Hulk win without completely destroying Manhattan in the process?
description.8: Scarlet Witch is confronted by Scarlet Witch.
description.9: Spider-Man has his hands tied with a super-army of Spider-Clones! Will the Jackal's maniacal plans be foiled at last?
description.11: Riger discovers that Kane is actually Malekith in disguise!
description.12: Guest-starring The Punisher! Frank Castle seeks vengeance against Jackal. But why is Spider-Man vying to keep the villain alive?
description.14: The team continues to struggle with Reed Richards' death, as the Human Torch leaves the Baxter Building for the Fantastic Force. Scott Lang gets a visit 'from a very special lady', while Lyja and company become Thing-like beings in a mission gone awry!
description.15: During an investigation at the city morgue, Wolverine attacks an innocent doctor. Has the feral mutant given into his savagery at last?
description.16: Without further resource, the X-Men call on James and Heather Hudson of Alpha Flight to uncover Wolverine's animalistic rage. Will Logan ever be the same since being stripped of his Adamantium? This is feral Wolverine- unhinged and unpredictable!
description.20: Cable and Professor X discuss their leadership styles while their respective teams spar off throughout the day. Meanwhile, Boomer is less than happy with Cannonball!
description.25: It's a full on Spider-Battle! Peter and Ben vs. Kaine, Spidercide and the Jackal! Which side will triumph in this Spider-Man Civil War?
description.26: Deathcry faces accusations from Mandroids and an overzealous Henry Gyrich. Her fellow teammates vouch for her heroism, but will their impassioned pleas be enough to convince the Feds? Plus, Deathcry receives a mysterious message from her home planet!
description.27: Has Steve Roger's life come to an end? Find out as the Sentinel of Liberty gets stalked by the Angel of Death!
description.29: With Rhino a (very) near victim of his alien suit, Spider-Man determines to rid himself of his extraterrestrial clinger-on. But a symbiote bond is hard to break. Adapting Spider-Man's ""Alien Suit Saga!""
description.31: All'spacelanes'lead to'Boonda'the'Hutt's palace! From one direction comes Olag Greck, looking to strike a shady deal, and from the other comes a drone barge loaded to the gunwales with angry'droids, among them a mysteriously transformed'See-Threepio!
description.32: Wedge Antilles is a combat-hardened X-wing pilot, one of the only fliers to survive the missions against both Death Stars. After those two assignments and his post as leader of Rogue Squadron, you'd think he'd seen everything. But when he heads a rescue and retrieval for a downed man on the planet Cilpar, he finds something he'd never expected: a culture that hates the Empire... and hates the Alliance even more!
description.33: Nightmare, the ruler of the The Nightmare Realm, is looking for a mighty successor…
description.39: Spidey is on trial for the murder of Louise Kennedy! With Carnage acting as the prosecutor, will our hero survive long enough to hear the sentence?
description.40: The island the Avengers have been fighting on deteriorates into an illusion of A.I.M. M.O.D.O.K. makes an ill-fated attempt to save reality, but time is not on his side. Witness the Super-Adaptoid make the ultimate sacrifice!
description.41: M.O.D.O.K. is back with a vengeance! Witness as Captain America battles both villains and heroes as his fight against A.I.M. continues!
description.42: Professor X and Cable have a private meeting which results in a big change for the X-Force team. While some are happy with the results, others disapprove strongly. Will this mean the end of X-Force?
description.47: What is ""Prometheum X""? Astronauts John Jameson and Paul Stevens unlock unlimited potential in a special alien compound… that turns out to be a sentient being. Adapting Spider-Man's ""Alien Suit Saga!""
description.49: The spy trade is a dangerous game, and if you lose you die. But there are greater dangers than death to those who cast false identities. There is the danger of forgetting who you are. In this second issue of Star Wars: River of Chaos, Leia is behind enemy lines with only a handful of Rebel spies at her command. But do they all want to break the Empire, or is there an Imperial in ally's clothing amongst them?
description.52: Force Works teams up with Earth's Mightiest Heroes - the Avengers! The heroes take the fight to the Kree cabal called Starstealth, to get revenge for the death of Wonder Man!
description.53: The show-stopping finale to the spectacular slugfest between Marvel's sinister symbiotes! The first domino of Cletus Kasady's murder spree is ready to fall, but can Eddie Brock overcome his inner demons - both figuratively and literally - and become the hero the city needs to stop Carnage?
description.56: Excalibur lands on Genosha and discovers mutants are being attacked and killed by humans with special bullets!
description.57: A routine SWAT op goes sour when the troops stumble into the Abomination! There's only one thing that can solve this crisis - a big, green thing!
description.58: Tony Stark's mentor Ted Slaght becomes his newest foe when he is transformed into Slag!
description.60: The only one who can clear Ben Reilly of murder is the man who hates him most of all: Kaine! In this issue we finally learn the shocking identity and origin of Kaine.
description.61: To save the well-being of the Asgardians and the Godpack, Thor goes to Hel and makes his comrades promise not to go and rescue him.
description.62: Peter Parker stands trial- for murder! The Trial of Peter Parker kicks off here!
description.65: The Fantastic Four get attacked by Thor, who is under a spell casted by Morgan Le Fay, the one responsible for the rising Atlantis. The Inhuman royal family continue their search for the Sub-Mariner and encounter the Fantastic Four at their meeting with NATO about Atlantis. Sub-mariner and the Inhumans battle it out for Atlantis and Thor regains consciousness and assists the Fantastic Four with their plans. Guest Starring: The Inhuman royal family, Namor the Sub-Mariner and Thor.
description.67: The X-Men share their concerns about teammate-gone-rogue Wolverine. Will his fellow mutants be able to pull Logan back from the edge? Or will the man be lost and become fully feral?
description.70: It's the Fantastic Four, Thor, Namor and more taking on Morgan Le Fey for the fate of Atlantis!
description.72: Jabba'has an old saying: If you can't beat 'em, buy 'em out! And that's just what he attempts to do when he encounters an unexpected nemesis on his journey through'the galaxy. But he may have to part with something more personal than his precious spice if he's going to close this deal!
description.73: Trapped on a drone barge headed for a recycling center,'See-Threepio'is about to have his memory wiped clean!'Artoo'races to rescue his old pal, but will Threepio even recognize the plucky little'droid'by the time he arrives?
description.81: With the Mind Gem in hand, Maxam's memories are restored to him, as well as his forgotten misson…to kill Adam Warlock! What is the secret behind this shocking revelation?
description.84: Strange has to protect our dimension from imminent danger! Some things never change.
description.88: Several months after the destruction of the Death Star, Emperor Palpatine sends an Imperial pilot to spy on the governor of a distant planet, M'haeli. Although Palpatine knows of certain Rebel activity on M'Haeli, he does not know of the presence of one particular Rebel: Princess Leia Organa! Can Leia undermine the enemy from within, or is she doomed to drown in a river of chaos? This ground-breaking four-issue series takes readers behind enemy lines, to see the Rebellion through the eyes of an officer of the Empire!
description.90: The Slorenian villains continue their campaign of revenge on Force Works, until Iron Man decides it's time to get a little payback for the payback! Plus, a back up adventure starring War Machine!
description.91: Venom is down…but is he out? Eddie Brock's slugfest with Carnage has left him seriously injured, as well as left Carnage unchecked in unleashing violence and chaos! Venom's rearing for another round, but what chance does he have?
description.94: The Incredible Hulk has the strength, but does he have the speed to keep up with Speedfreek?
description.95: Desperate times call for desperate measures: Tony Stark dons the Crimson Dynamo armor to battle Titanium Man.
description.96: Dr. Judas Traveller unleashes his full villainy in CROSSFIRE, PART 2!
description.97: Thor, Sif, the High Evolutionary and Godpack are still not enough to fight off Kurse's monsters!
description.98: Peter encounters a familiar face...in Gwen Stacy? Warren Miles reflects on his life with his new wife.

0.text: An extradimensional adventure! In the medieval land of Geshem, Wolverine is approached by Shaman (Professor X), to stop the homicidal rampage of a man known only as Beast. Wolverine must fight for the honor of Queen Rain…and for the safety of Geshem’s citizens!

2.text: Venom, Ben Reilly and Peter Parker visit a planet inhabited solely by symbiotes!

3.text: Spidercide, Jackal's personal Spider-Man clone, releases a mass virus created by his master.

4.text: The payback for Wonder Man comes down to this! The combined strength of Force Works and the Avengers against the alien might of the Kree enforcers known as Starstealth! Who will come out on top?

5.text: Matt Murdock soul searches as he goes in and out of consciousness and tests all of his violent personalities.

10.text: While on their way back from Mexico, Miguel and Xina discover that a new player has taken control of the United States…and his name is President Doom! Meanwhile, Dana gets on the wrong side of a mysterious intruder.

19.text: Ben heads to Salt Lake City in search of work. Little does he know that another clone, the individual known as Kaine, is hot on his trail!
Ben Reilly has just discovered that he is a clone of Peter Parker. Lost and alone, he begins to wander aimlessly in the hope that he will discover a new life and a new direction.

20.text: Cable and Professor X discuss their leadership styles while their respective teams spar off throughout the day. Meanwhile, Boomer is less than happy with Cannonball!

21.text: Sugar Man dispatches another player from the Age of Apocalypse timeline. Rex is after Nate!

23.text: A new Sin-Eater emerges, and he's keen to turn Eddie Brock's (that's Venom to you) life upside down!

24.text: Marvel's favorite pessimist looks through his darkest glass yet into a world where "marvel" is just another word for "horror." Nuclear warfare, internment camps, government oppression, drug addiction, degradation, suicide...and those are just the ones we have words for.

28.text: Tyler Stone hatches a plot that goes far beyond Doom’s impeachment. Meanwhile, top financiers continue to elude the newly instated President.

30.text: The X-Men come across the Starjammers and one of the X-Men reunites with someone long forgotten.

33.text: Nightmare, the ruler of the The Nightmare Realm, is looking for a mighty successor…

34.text: Emma Frost has been kidnapped by the deadly Gene Nation!  Will her young trainees be strong enough to save her from these fearsome foes?

36.text: ZOMBIES ON THE LOOSE! Miguel, Gabriel, and the ladies party it up for a Day of the Dead festival. No better way to celebrate than with the living dead, right?

37.text: The Trial of Peter Parker concludes! Dr. Trainer reaches the wrong conclusion about Spider-Man's true identity...mistaking Ben Reilly as the real Peter Parker!

38.text: Cable and Domino try to pick up the pieces after all the chaos, but their short-lived rerpieve doesn't last long! Cable's old friend Blaquesmith is in danger, and Cable is the only man that can help him!

42.text: Professor X and Cable have a private meeting which results in a big change for the X-Force team. While some are happy with the results, others disapprove strongly. Will this mean the end of X-Force?

43.text: A disoriented Nate is discovered by Madelyne Pryor upon his arrival to our dimension from the Age of Apocalypse.

46.text: When a betrayer is discovered in his midst, Doom nearly destabilizes the office of the Presidency!

47.text: What is “Prometheum X”? Astronauts John Jameson and Paul Stevens unlock unlimited potential in a special alien compound… that turns out to be a sentient being. Adapting Spider-Man’s “Alien Suit Saga!”

48.text: Liandra of the Shi'ar Empire might be able to explain what's happened to Jean, but first the X-Men must face the return of Juggernaut!

50.text: Ben, Peter and Eddie Brock are New York's only hope against a symbiote attack!

52.text: Force Works teams up with Earth's Mightiest Heroes - the Avengers! The heroes take the fight to the Kree cabal called Starstealth, to get revenge for the death of Wonder Man!

53.text: The show-stopping finale to the spectacular slugfest between Marvel's sinister symbiotes! The first domino of Cletus Kasady's murder spree is ready to fall, but can Eddie Brock overcome his inner demons - both figuratively and literally - and become the hero the city needs to stop Carnage?

54.text: The One Who Knows must fight the Pathbreaker and get to Vesper in order to find Kismet, his possible mother!

55.text: After getting betrayed by an employee, Kingpin tries to kill and frame them for the murder of Glorianna. The employee wakes up deformed and attacks Foggy.  Daredevil and Kingpin team up to defend Foggy and fight the creature.

64.text: The Age of Apocalypse has ended...but what new threats await the X-Men, X-Factor, X-Force and all mutants?  Plus, what Age of Apocalypse heroes and villains have crossed over to our reality?

68.text: Amelia Voght turns to Scott and Jean for help!

75.text: Bishop and Storm do battle with the dread Madri Priests! Meanwhile, Quicksilver and Banshee attempt to find Jamie Madrox. But does Madrox even want to be found?

77.text: The council readies the attack against Apocalypse. But Apocalypse is prepared for them. Can the heroes finally end the Age of Apocalypse or will they be cast down into oblivion? Plus, Wolverine's secret weapon revealed!

79.text: Magneto has been taken prisoner by Apocalypse! Nate Grey battles Sinister! The key to victory is revealed! All in this issue!

81.text: With the Mind Gem in hand, Maxam's memories are restored to him, as well as his forgotten misson…to kill Adam Warlock! What is the secret behind this shocking revelation?

82.text: Husk and Vicente have their back against a wall as the Sugar Man bears down on them! The only person that can save them is the steel-skinned Colossus! Prepare for Sugar Man versus Colossus-winner takes all!

84.text: Strange has to protect our dimension from imminent danger! Some things never change.

86.text: DAY OF THE DEAD! Zombies roam the streets after a mass reincarnation enacted by Fernando Morgez. Spider-Man is temporarily blinded and hospitalized!

89.text: Eddie Brock may be pushing back against his symbiote host, Venom. Plus: Spider-Man vs. the Neo-Luddites!

90.text: The Slorenian villains continue their campaign of revenge on Force Works, until Iron Man decides it's time to get a little payback for the payback! Plus, a back up adventure starring War Machine!

91.text: Venom is down…but is he out? Eddie Brock's slugfest with Carnage has left him seriously injured, as well as left Carnage unchecked in unleashing violence and chaos! Venom's rearing for another round, but what chance does he have?

93.text: Wilson Fisk and Kruel have a feud that originated ages ago.  After their battle, Wilson Fisk eliminated Kruel’s memories and now, Kruel will stop at nothing to get revenge on this mystery man.

99.text: The final battle for the Age of Apocalypse is here - Apocalypse vs. Magneto and his X-Men.  Can these heroes set reality right and topple Apocalypse once and for all?
